ZH: 他试图用暴力恐吓我。
EN: He tried to intimidate me with violence.

ZH: 不要被他的恐吓所吓倒。
EN: Don't be intimidated by his threats.

ZH: 她收到了一封匿名信，内容充满了恐吓。
EN: She received an anonymous letter filled with threats.

ZH: 这种恐吓行为不可取。
EN: Such intimidating behavior is unacceptable.

ZH: 别让任何人恐吓你。
EN: Don't let anyone intimidate you.

ZH: 那些黑帮分子企图对他施加恐吓。
EN: The gangsters attempted to intimidate him.

ZH: 我不会屈服于恐吓。
EN: I won't succumb to intimidation.

ZH: 他用恐吓的方式威胁我。
EN: He threatened me in an intimidating manner.

ZH: 这是一种恐吓行为。
EN: This is a form of intimidation.

ZH: 警察袭击了黑社会分子，以示恐吓。
EN: The police carried out a raid on the mafia as a show of intimidation.

ZH: 她感到害怕，因为恐吓信越来越频繁。
EN: She became scared as the threatening letters became more frequent.

ZH: 我们不能容忍任何形式的恐吓。
EN: We cannot tolerate any form of intimidation.

ZH: 孩子们不应该受到恐吓。
EN: Children should not be subjected to intimidation.

ZH: 他们希望通过威胁和恐吓来控制我们。
EN: They hope to control us through threats and intimidation.

ZH: 我们不能被这种行为所恐吓。
EN: We cannot be intimidated by such behavior.

ZH: 这是对人权的恐吓。
EN: This is intimidation against human rights.

ZH: 她勇敢地面对恐吓。
EN: She bravely faced the intimidation.

ZH: 恐吓只会让他们更加团结。
EN: Intimidation will only make them more united.

ZH: 恐吓是很不道德的手段。
EN: Intimidation is a very unethical tactic.

ZH: 我们不能允许任何人使用恐吓来迫使我们屈服。
EN: We cannot allow anyone to use intimidation to force us to submit.
